# Rule 5: LSASS Memory Dumping Detected
# --------------------------------------------------
# Description: Detects attempts to access or dump the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS) 
# memory, which is a common technique used by tools like Mimikatz or ProcDump to steal credentials.
# 
# MITRE ATT&CK: T1003.001 (OS Credential Dumping: LSASS Memory)
# Severity: Critical
# 
# Logic (Sigma-style):
#   - TargetImage: 'C:\Windows\System32\lsass.exe'
#   - GrantedAccess: ('0x1010' OR '0x1fffff')
#   - CallTrace contains: ('dbghelp.dll' OR 'psapi.dll')
# 
# Log Source: Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon (Event ID 10: ProcessAccess)
